# /check-flow — End-to-End Flow Verification

## Purpose
Verify integrity of flows between frontend and backend: types, endpoints, and environment variables.

## 1. Types/DTOs Verification
Compare frontend interfaces/types with backend response models:
{{#modulesOfRole "frontend"}}
- **{{name}}**: `{{directory}}/src/types/` — interfaces the frontend expects
{{/modulesOfRole}}
{{#modulesOfRole "backend"}}
- **{{name}}**: `{{directory}}/src/` — response models/schemas
{{/modulesOfRole}}

**Per-type checklist:**
- [ ] Required fields present on both sides
- [ ] Compatible types (string/number/boolean/Date)
- [ ] Optional fields marked correctly
- [ ] Enums synchronized

## 2. Endpoint Verification
Verify frontend API calls match backend routes:
{{#modulesOfRole "frontend"}}
- **{{name}}**: `{{directory}}/src/services/` — HTTP calls
{{/modulesOfRole}}
{{#modulesOfRole "backend"}}
- **{{name}}**: `{{directory}}/src/` — defined routes/endpoints
{{/modulesOfRole}}

**Per-endpoint checklist:**
- [ ] URL path exists in backend
- [ ] Correct HTTP method (GET/POST/PUT/DELETE)
- [ ] Path/query parameters compatible
- [ ] Request body compatible with expected schema
{{#ifRule "api-response-contract"}}
- [ ] Response follows standard envelope: `{ "data": ... }` or `{ "error": ... }`
{{/ifRule}}

## 3. Environment Variables Verification
- Verify all `process.env.*` or `os.environ.*` references exist in `.env.example`
- Verify no critical variables are missing

## Report
For each verification, generate:
```
=== Check Flow ===
[Types]    ComponentX ↔ EndpointY: ✅ Compatible / ❌ Field Z missing
[Endpoint] GET /api/resource: ✅ Exists / ❌ Not found
[Env]      API_URL: ✅ Defined / ❌ Missing in .env.example
```
{{/if}}
